Author: phm87#7395
Content:
``Channels can stay open indefinitely: as long as the two parties in the channel continue to cooperate with each other, the channel can stay open indefinitely -- there is no mandatory timeout period. This can further reduce the load on the blockchain as well as allow the fees for opening and closing the channel to be amortized over a longer period of time.``
https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Lightning_Network

Author: phm87#7395
Content: it seems you are right

Author: phm87#7395
Content: about nota, btc tx from iguana are using 1* address (legacy) that have high fee tx. A tx from 3* address is segwit enabled and retrocompatible so it can send to a 3* or 1*. And there is the last one cb* (?) that is segwit only

Author: phm87#7395
Content: but if you close the channel, you'll get back your funds after a certain time (counted in blocks)
